content.body:
### Shop LT265/75R16 Tire Size The LT265/75R16 is exclusively a light truck tire size; it can be found on trucks like the Chevy Silverado 1500, RAM 1500, Ford Excursion, Nissan Pathfinder and Chevrolet Tahoe (usually older models). For most drivers of SUVs and light trucks, all-season tires offer a good balance of ride quality, low noise and year-round traction. For all-season tires in the LT265/75R16 size, we’d recommend tires like the Michelin Defender LTX M/S, [Bridgestone Dueler H/L Alenza Plus](https://simpletire.com/brands/bridgestone-tires/dueler-h-l-alenza-plus), Falken Wildpeak H/T02, Nokian One H/T, or Kumho Crugen HT51. Popular vehicles: 1999-2006 Chevrolet Silverado 1500
2015-2018 RAM 1500
1999-2005 Ford Excursion
2005-2012 Nissan Pathfinder
1995-2006 Chevrolet Tahoe Of course, a lot of light trucks are equipped with 4WD, making all-terrain tires a great choice. All-terrain tires make it easy to go off-road and have no problem with rocks, gravel, sand, mud and soft soil, thanks to their reinforced carcass and aggressive tread design. For premium all-terrain tires in LT265/75R16, we’d recommend the Pirelli Scorpion All Terrain Plus, Falken Wildpeak A/T3W, [Nitto Ridge Grappler](https://simpletire.com/brands/nitto-tires/ridge-grappler), and Yokohama Geolandar X-AT. Some drivers of bigger light trucks enjoy taking their ride off-road quite a bit, so they might need a set of mud terrain tires for extra grip and performance on tough terrains. Consider the Toyo Open Country M/T, BFGoodrich Mud-Terrain T/A KM3, General Grabber X3, and [Hankook Dynapro MT2 RT05](https://simpletire.com/brands/hankook-tires/dynapro-mt2-rt05) to help your light truck conquer the toughest terrains. Whether you drive a Chevrolet Tahoe, Ford Excursion, RAM 1500 or something else, SimpleTire has a set of LT265/75R16 tires that meets your needs at a great price!
